trans-unit.source: Exposes properties that contain federation settings that control the behavior of the WS-Federation Authentication Module (<xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.WSFederationAuthenticationModule"></xref>) and the Session Authentication Module (<xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.SessionAuthenticationModule"></xref>) in web applications.
trans-unit.target: Viser egenskaper som inneholder federation innstillinger som kontrollerer virkemåten for modulen WS Federation godkjenning (<xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.WSFederationAuthenticationModule"></xref>) og økten godkjenning Module (<xref href="System.IdentityModel.Services.SessionAuthenticationModule"></xref>) i webprogrammer.

trans-unit.source: By default web applications have a single FederationConfiguration object that is accessed through the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.FederatedAuthentication.FederationConfiguration?displayProperty=fullName> property.
trans-unit.target: Som standard webprogrammer har ett enkelt FederationConfiguration-objekt som er tilgjengelig via den <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.FederatedAuthentication.FederationConfiguration?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.FederatedAuthentication.FederationConfiguration?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: The first time the property is accessed a new FederationConfiguration instance is initialized from settings in the configuration file and the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.FederatedAuthentication.FederationConfigurationCreated?displayProperty=fullName> event is raised.
trans-unit.target: Første gang egenskapen får tilgang til et nytt FederationConfiguration forekomsten er initialisert fra innstillinger i konfigurasjonsfilen og <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.FederatedAuthentication.FederationConfigurationCreated?displayProperty=fullName>denne hendelsen oppstår.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.FederatedAuthentication.FederationConfigurationCreated?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: You can use the properties and methods exposed by the FederationConfiguration class to modify or replace the object initialized from configuration in an event handler.
trans-unit.target: Du kan bruke egenskaper og metoder som vises av klassen FederationConfiguration å endre eller erstatte objektet initialisert fra konfigurasjonen i en hendelsesbehandling.

trans-unit.source: This object is available through the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfigurationCreatedEventArgs.FederationConfiguration%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property inside the event handler.
trans-unit.target: Dette objektet er tilgjengelig via den <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfigurationCreatedEventArgs.FederationConfiguration%2A?displayProperty=fullName>egenskapen i hendelsesbehandlingen.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfigurationCreatedEventArgs.FederationConfiguration%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: The `system.identityModel` section must be specified in a `<section>` element under the `<configSections>` element in the configuration file or an exception is thrown.
trans-unit.target: Den `system.identityModel` delen må angis i en `<section>` elementet under den `<configSections>` er et element i konfigurasjonsfilen eller et unntak.

trans-unit.source: ``` <configSections> <section name="system.identityModel" type="System.IdentityModel.Configuration.SystemIdentityModelSection, System.IdentityModel, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=B77A5C561934E089" /> </configSections> ``` If `loadConfig` is `true` and only a single `<federationConfiguration>` element is specified, settings are loaded using that element.
trans-unit.target: ``` <configSections> <section name="system.identityModel" type="System.IdentityModel.Configuration.SystemIdentityModelSection, System.IdentityModel, Version=4.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=B77A5C561934E089" /> </configSections> ```Hvis `loadConfig` er `true` og bare ett `<federationConfiguration>` elementet er angitt, innstillinger er lastet inn med dette elementet.

trans-unit.source: If multiple `<federationConfiguration>` elements are specified, the method attempts to load settings from the element that is unnamed of that has the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfiguration.DefaultFederationConfigurationName>.
trans-unit.target: Hvis flere `<federationConfiguration>` elementer er angitt, metoden forsøk på å laste inn innstillingene fra element som uten navn som har <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfiguration.DefaultFederationConfigurationName>.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfiguration.DefaultFederationConfigurationName>

trans-unit.source: If such an element does not exist, the method returns without loading settings.
trans-unit.target: Hvis slikt element ikke finnes, returnerer metoden uten å laste inn innstillingene.

trans-unit.source: This results in an exception when the <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfiguration.Initialize%2A> method is called.
trans-unit.target: Dette resulterer i et unntak under den <xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfiguration.Initialize%2A>-metoden.</xref:System.IdentityModel.Services.Configuration.FederationConfiguration.Initialize%2A>

trans-unit.source: > [!WARNING] > Microsoft recommends that if you specify multiple `<federationConfiguration>` elements in the `system.identityModel.services` configuration section that at least one of them is unnamed or has its name set to an empty string.
trans-unit.target: > [!WARNING] > Anbefales det at hvis du angir flere `<federationConfiguration>` elementer i den `system.identityModel.services` konfigurasjonsdelen at minst én av dem uten navn eller ikke har navnet satt til en tom streng.
